storyText: I know this fight is wrong.
But I must for my wish...
Heh heh. You're torn! Now whatya gonna do?
Should I or shouldn't I?\nTo kill or not to kill?
You know we'll keep\nour promise, don't you?
I can't trust either of you in the least.
Put an end to\ntheir useless existences.
I have my own reasons for\nwanting my author revived.
But to kill others for\nmy own personal gain...
You who are a slave to a\nselfish sense of "justice."
Save it for someone who cares.
It seems you do have a belief,\nand yet, you're still uneasy.
We might have more in common than I thought.
Do that, and your\nwishes will come true.
If I continue to fight,\nI will be certain in my desires.
Hee hee hee...\nThis is a nightmare.
But the way it looks...\nIt's strangely familiar.
I wish to tell these\npuppets to go to hell.
I have my own reasons to fight.
Those puppets will\nsoon get their due.
It smells. It's loud.\nKeep it away.
Nothing to do with meâ€¦\nNope, nothing at all.
Heh heh heh.\nYou sure about that?
Even if you avert your eyes\nand cover your ears...
There's no escape!\nYou have to fight!
This is the path I choose.\nAll for my author.
Kill everything in your way.\nRip off their arms!
Such a strong woman!\nYou can do it, Snow!
Strength doesn't matter.\nI do what's just.
I know what I do\nis right.
About what? My path?\nOr my feelings?
That is a pointless question.\nI'm not conflicted in the least.
That's right! I mean,\nyou are justice after all.
Yes! Kill the bad guys!\nTear off their legs!
But it's bad, isn't it?\nIt isn't justice, is it?
Off with their heads!\nOff with all of their heads!
I'd risk my life\nto save him.
Huh. Guess your life\nisn't worth a damn.
This will be the first and last\ntime I team up with you.
Any more of this, and we'll end up killing each other.
I want to cleanse\nthe world of you.
"You piss me off, so I want to kill you."\nThere. Fixed it.
People like you never know when to quit.
How about you and me finish the job at hand?
The enemy? Naturally,\nI will destroy it!
A more amusing tale\nwould be nice.
Cinder as a queen?!\nI'd pay to see that!
Right? That's why I must kill\neverything in my way.
Of course. I especially love catching them by surprise.
Hate to break it to you,\nbut that thing is dead, girl.
Hehe. Hansel...\nNo more sweets for you.
If you have a sore tooth,\nI'll remove it for you.
Word of advice, sister.\nSeek help. Professional help.
Quiet, witch!\nWe'll toss you in the pot!
There's your witch! Look!\nThe enemy, over there!
You witch...\nI'll kill you! KILL YOU!
Well, they may prove\nuseful for something.
Oh dear. Is that the maiden's heart coming up for air?
Shut it, doll. You want to die?
It takes guts to wear\nthose shoes.
A revolting look-alike\nif you ask me!
You even have the same face. Disgusting, isn't it?
Bah! I don't care.\nIt's in my way, so it dies.
I'll do my best if my\nbrother insists on it.
Brother? What brother?\nAll we see is a head!
Not likely!\nI mean, her brother is reallyâ€”
I'm a bad girl.\nThat's why... That's why...
Keh heh heh!\nYou make no sense!
Hey, Hansel. What\nshould we make next?
Just make sure you\ndon't eat too much!
The evil witch will\nfind you if you do.
She just keeps talking to herself.
It's gross! She weirds me out!
Well, it's him for sure.\nBut yeah, a nightmare.
Oh, Hansel. Come!\nGive me a hug!
Ugh, this again.\nShe just won't listen.
It's obvious she's one bird\nshort of a birdcage.
Where is he?\nBring him to me!
Ugh. You'll have to\ndo that yourself.
That's the reason for\nall of this killing!
I see. Then I guess\nI should kill more.
I'll kill more and\nmore and more.
I'm not afraid.\nNot if it's for you, Hansel.
It will. It's worn out.\nSmash it to bits!
Then I'll kill the rest\nof you for waking me.
Whoa! What a show\nof anger and rage!
Wake up or die!\nYou don't wanna die, do ya?
I'm sleepy...\nI'll sleep...when I want to.
Hey... I'm done fighting,\nso can I sleep now?
It was such a\nnice nap, too...
Now you've done it!\nShe's getting angry!
You were so sleepy...\nSo I thought I'd give you eternal sleep!
Hey, what are you\ntwo messing around for?
Don't you know all that\nnoise will attract the enemy?
I'm done with you after this last kill!
Done with me?\nAre... Are you gonna die?
Can't sleep?\nGo ahead if you want.
I have a bad feeling\nthat I can't shake off...
Wow. She even sleeps\nas a nightmare.
Her posture will\nmake her go numb!
Try knocking it outta\nbed to find out!
Sacrifices are needed\nto revive your Author!
So, what are you\nkilling and why?
Oh, just everybody, I guess.\nBecause it's so much fun!
Don't forget about your author\neither, you hear?
Oh boy, do I! I wanna have even more fun!
It looks just like me!\nI love it!
Boo! You're no fun!\nNoya? How about you?
Wanna play with me?\nI wanna play!
This is no fun.\nI just wanna play!
Sacrifices must be made\nto revive your author.
You'll kill lots of\nenemies for us, right?
If I must.\nI will give it all I can.
When I finally revive him, I'll... Hehehe.
Oh... This is splendid.\nI love strong people.
Oh my! How deplorable!\nI could never...
I desire greater pleasure.\nI feel naught but pain.
My name is Kaguya.\nIt's a pleasure to meet you.
So what shall we\nattend to first?
Well, um, it'd be nice\nif you'd decide.
I personally prefer it\nwhen others command me.
I'm no good at\nleading the way.
If it is what is best,\nit is what we shall do.
If you're\ngoing to fight, then so will I...
You know nobody likes\na bully, right?
This Princess Kaguya...\nShe's a bit of a nympho, huh?
But you look like\nsomeone who wants to be punished.
Hey, what if you tried\nto be the dominator for once?
Oh, if only someone\nwould bind me and...
Someone who really wants to be punished, right?
Look at her blush!\nShe admits it! She's a nympho!
That one is truly strong,\nis he not?
Get a grip, lady!\nIt's a dragon!
Whoa. Wow. Whoa.\nShe's a nympho, alright.
You know you have to kill to revive your author.
No! That was all\nthe staff's doing!
I mean it. Seriously...\nI can't do anything on my own.
Don't you have a will\nof your own?
A will?\nI used to be a puppet.
Yes, but not now!\nNow you're free!
Free? I'm not sure\nI like freedom...
You know this is a\nfairy tale world, right?
B-But there are no dragons in my fairy tale!
Too bad.\nThen again, this isn't your tale.
If it was a shark,\nI'd at least know what to do!
If anyone's nose is going to grow, it's going to be mine, right?
If your nose grew,\nyou'd be a monster!
No lie! It is!\nIt's definitely Pinocchio!
But it's a Pinocchio\nshrouded in darkness!
Oh! Alice looks like her\nheart is about to break!
Heh heh! "Sad" is only two letters\naway from "glad."
True. So close,\nyet so far way.
The characters want the\nauthors who made them.
The parent who gave birth to 'em?
Alice the Bound\nand Snow the Just.
Those fools do nothing but fight.
Yeah, they're\nboth smiling, inside and out.
They don't know the\nhellish suffering that awaits them.
Their smiles look like\nthose of children.
We'd revive their author if they\nkilled the nightmares.
But how many do they\nhave to kill?
You know what they call Nightmares\nin Japan? "Naitomea."
How did they earn such\na terrible name?
What makes a dream\ninto a nightmare?
So many characters\nall in one place.
I wonder how they'll survive\nin this chaotic world.
But it's too late.\nNo turning back.
She believes she's right.\nNo doubt about it.
She doesn't know the\nvalue of the life she takes.
Blind faith, blind obedience.\nNo thinking allowed!
Is blind belief the\nkey to strength?
We'll have her kill\nso many for us.
For as long as her\nfaith holds up!
Even if they realize their mistake,\nthey can't turn back.
The road back was\nblocked off long ago.
Justice is reckless!\nKee hee hee hee!
Will it scare her to know\nthe enemy is herself?
Good point. That wouldn't\nbe just, would it?
Snow White and Cinderella,\ntogether at last!
Let's sit back and see\nwhat happens.
The showdown between\nJustice and Depravity begins!
I bet the Authors would\nthink this was just great!
Even though she\nneeds a prince for that?
But this Cinderella\nis a little different.
How do you think\nher tale will unfold?
What do you think\nof the killing?
Those who were abused\nwant to abuse.
Those who were hated\nwant to hate.
What do you think of these two?
I mean, words don't\nget through to her.
The witch trigger always\ngets her going!
She loves them.\nThat much is sure.
Well, of course.\nI mean, those slippers...
Are her only anchor\nto her heart.
What if somebody took\nthem from her?
Oh, that would be bad!\nBut so very amusing!
Such tenacity...\nShe's made of strong stuff.
I bet she can't\neven see us.
I bet she can't\neven hear us.
Her heart is lost in\na deep, deep forest...
No way it can talk.\nHave you gone mad, too?
No way it can hear.\nYou have gone mad.
But that won't stop\nher from apologizing to him.
Wrench the head's mouth open\nand make it eat treats.
The witch is the guilty\none, isn't she?
He can't get fat if\nit's only his head.
I know. I know.\nI just can't help myselfâ™ª
I get it, but I wish\nI didn'tâ™ª
Oh! Not even bad\ndreams phase her!
She wants to relive\nthe bad dreams.
Well, if you want\nto revive someone...
Is there a certain\nfuture she's after?
What happens if you\nbreak them more?
What does she need\nto sleep soundly?
A quiet place with\nno one around.
Wake her on the wrong side\nof the bed, and you're dead.
Her Author is also\nasleep, in a way...
She'd die if we\nleft her alone.
I doubt she'd mind\nall that much...
But that's not much\nof a story...
Disturb her sleep\nand watch her rage!
Yeah... But her desire\nfor sleep is TOO strong.
Beauty and Red.\nWhat a cute couple!
Uh oh. Sleeping Beauty\nlooks reeaally pissed!
I feel bad for\nRed Riding Hood.
Is there ever a time\nwhere she can't sleep?
But that's the best time\nto close your eyes.
So you don't see\nthe pain coming...
What kicks would you get from\nhaving two of yourself around?
Even if you like the other you,\nwould you set it free?
If you let it do the\nthings you want to do.
You'd get angry, right?\nWouldn't you be upset?
Then what would you do\nabout the other you?
If it were me...\nKeh heh heh!
Why give a blade\nto someone crazy?
So they can kill\nwhenever they want.
It's like giving them\na license to kill!
It's not like they're\nkilling for the hell of it.
Red Riding Hood sure\nseems to be enjoying it...
Yeah. Killing is like\nplaying to her.
She only lives\nto play and kill.
Have fun playing with\nRed Riding Hood!
Oh, no, no, no!\nWait for me!
Just to be at peace,\nthank the maker!
Ugh, I've never met\nanyone so difficult!
It's as if killing\nis her true love.
A maiden's heart works\nin mysterious ways!
She may deny it,\nbut them eyes of hers don't.
We'll have to give\nher what she wants.
We'll have to make her\nfight a strong Nightmare!
Princess Kaguya the Masochist.\nPinocchio the Dependent.
Pinocchio would never\nthink to punish Kaguya.
Kaguya would never think\nto lead Pinocchio.
A never-ending cycle\nof unfulfilled desires. It's really annoying to watch.
What if we brought in\nSnow White?
Not unless we want her to end\nup with a hole in her belly.
Not unless we want to end\nup with holes in our bellies.
Fine! Then let's get all\nthese brats together!
Does she want to be\npunished a certain way?
Doesn't she know that picky people\ndon't get a choice in the end?
Could be the pride she takes\nin being a nympho...
They're nymphos that just want to\nbe punished by everybody!
Does that mean the\nNightmare is, too?
That would make her\na next-level nympho!
She seems to enjoy being\npunished by herself!
Someone who will punish\nher all she wants.
Did she find the one\nshe was looking for?
She found the one\nwho can overwhelm her!
That puppet can't make\nup his own mind.
Don't worry about that.\nHe has a secret weapon.
It's why he has blood\non his hands, though.
Will he act like\na puppet forever?
Being told what\nto do is easier.
Yeah, and that's\nhuman in a way!
What will he do\nabout the dragon?
Isn't it about time he\nexerted his own will?
Not gonna happen!\nThis is Pinocchio, after all.
Wood-for-brains does whatever\nthe twisted staff tells him to!
A wish to make\na puppet human!
Poor thing.\nLike a dog in the rain!
Is that rain or\nhis own tears?
Must be a lot of\npent-up emotion.
If it's a matter of\nlife or death...
Do you think he will\nfight for his life?
Do Nightmares have\na will of their own?
A will? A will? A will?!\nKehehehe!
Better get it down on paper then!\nKeh heh heh heh!
Heh heh. You really know\nhow to treat a lady.
A talking spider!\nDo spiders have backbones?
Do Nightmares...possess\na will of their own?
It's true.\nHe may be ugly on the outside, but he has heart.
The Nightmare that invades our hearts and minds...
I shall now depart\nto find him!
She is a lively one,\nisn't she?
I will not hesitate to resort to the lowest of lows.
Etch your sweet love\ninto my longing heart!
Oh, how sad!\nSuch a pure desire!
It'd be nice if it\ncame true.
So smash...\nSmash 'til it has no shape!
If anybody can do it,\nshe can!
Sounds like a small\nchild, doesn't it?
I'm scared! Save me!\nI hate 'em all!
Do you get it?\nDo you get it now?
It was once a child.\nAn innocent child.
Oh! It's so sad!\nPoor thing didn't wanna die!
Nice of us to go easy\non you though, right?
Aren't you sick of this yet?
Aren't you tired of this yet?
I'll keep fighting\nuntil victory is mine.
Don't you think\nthey feel the same?
You mean that ugly\nblob of desire?
The decision...\nis my own to make.
At last, one who\nis worthy of me.
I'm glad you asked, because it's NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.
I'm kinda weak.\nDo you mind if I...tag along?
I-I see.\nI-I'll be on my way, then.
Keh heh heh!\nTwo at once, huh?
Keh heh heh.\nLooks just like him.
Why do we all\nhave to fight?
Is it less scary if\nyou fight for them?
The staff and your will\nare one.
Throw the staff away\nif you want.
But can you make\ndecisions on your own?
I'll decide for you.\nStick with me.
Oh? So you already know\nwho to depend on?
Then keep that ridiculous staff. It's perfect for you!
No... I'll kill you.\nKill you all...
Right on time.\nGod I was bored of the wooden one.
The staff tells me to,\nso I will.
There you go again!\nIt's the staff's fault!
Everything you do!\nIt's the staff's fault!
Yes. I mean,\nit is what I am after all.
I can kill them any way I want, right?
Life for subsistence.\nYou don't feel anything?
Why should I?\nIt's only natural, right?
Get wise or get roasted, pig!
Heh heh. Hard to\nswallow, isn't it?
Am I...ugly?\nIs that why I'll die?
The prince only had\neyes for the beautiful.
Everything ugly will\nbe left for dead!
Don't you see how\nugly you are?
Heh. Don't sweat it.\nI need your guidance.
What will happen once you're\nno longer useful?
I don't like that\nlook in her eyes!
If the ugly cry,\nnobody hears them.
That's right. If you\nwant to be heard...
Come and sit.\nYou must be lonely.
We share with each\nother when happy.
The closest family\nin the whole world.
A happy day when we\nall get together.
We all put a smile\non Mother's face.
Why us? Why do you\ntake from us?
I'll grow the family\nand get her praise.
